1.5 critical masses  = 1-2 kilotons<br>
1.6 critical masses = 3-4 kilotons<br>
1.7 critical masses = 4-5 kilotons<br>
1.8 critical masses 6-7 kilotons<br>
1.9 critical masses = 7-8 kilotons.<br>
2 critical masses = 8-9 kilotons<br>
2.1 critical masses = 10-11 kilotons<br>
2.2 critical masses = 12-13 kilotons.<br>
2.25 critical masses = 15-16 kilotons<br>
2.5 critical masses = 18-20 kilotons<br>
2.75 critical masses = 28-30 kilotons<br>
3.0 critical masses = 40-45 kilotons<br>
4.0 critical masses = 50-80 kilotons.<br>
5.0 critical masses = 80-100 kilotons.<br>
